{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce Citizens\u2019 Referendum System for Legislation",
        "additional_details": "In our view, the UK\u2019s current system gives citizens no direct say on the agreement or rejection of legislation between general elections. Switzerland allows its citizens to vote on legislation multiple times per year. We think this produces more accountable government, greater civic trust, and long-term political stability. We believe that giving UK citizens powers to initiate referendums on legislation could reduce political disillusionment, force Parliament to reflect genuine public will, and bring Britain in line with modern democratic standards seen in Switzerland.",
        "background": "Introduce a citizens\u2019 initiated referendum system, allowing the public to propose and vote directly on legislation when a minimum signature threshold is reached, modelled on Switzerland\u2019s direct democracy system, which has operated successfully for over 150 years.",
